In either the three Sapphic Odes of Book F our together, or in the Carm. Saec. alone, there are twice as many instances of it as in the twenty-one Odes of the earlier Books.

There is no synaphea, but hypermetric syllables are occasionally elided at the end of all the first three verses of the stanza (2. 2. 18, 2. 16. 34, 4. 2. 22, 23, C. S. 47).
